There exists a basis $\vec{u_1}, \ldots, \vec{u_n}$ of $\R^n$ with $\vec{u_i} \cdot \vec{u_j} = \delta_{i, j}$ ($1$ if $i = j$ and $0$ otherwise) and real numbers $\lambda_1, \ldots, \lambda_n$($\lambda_i = \lambda_j$ possible) such that
\[
    A\vec{u_i} = \lambda_i\vec{u_i}
\] 
\[
    \vec{X} = \sum_{j=1}^{n} y_j\vec{u_j}
\] 
\[
    \vec{X} \cdot \vec{u_i} = \sum_{j=1}^{n} y_j\vec{u_j}\vec{u_i} = y_i
\] 

